'''''Street Sports Basketball''''' is a [[1987 in video gaming|1987]] [[computer game|computer]] [[basketball]] game for the [[IBM PC compatible|IBM PC]], [[Amstrad CPC]], [[Amiga]], [[Apple II series|Apple II]], [[Commodore 64]] and [[ZX Spectrum]]. It was developed by [[Epyx]] and [[video game publisher|published]] by [[U.S. Gold]].<ref>{{cite web | title=Street Sports Basketball (1987) | website=MobyGames | date=2000-02-27 | url=https://www.mobygames.com/game/400/street-sports-basketball/ | access-date=2023-10-22}}</ref>

== Gameplay ==
The game features a 3-a-side basketball match. Each team is made by three players with different skills chosen from the neighbours.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thelegacy.de/Museum/game.php3?titel_id=7068&game_id=7146|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110520190141/http://www.thelegacy.de/Museum/game.php3?titel_id=7068&game_id=7146 |archive-date=2011-05-20|title=Street Sports Basketball}}</ref>

